text: Ziegler's tree frog (Gracixalus ziegleri) is a frog. It lives in Vietnam. People have seen this frog 2200 meters above sea level. The adult frog is 28.1 â€“ 30.5 mm long from nose to rear end. The skin of the frog's back is brown to light brown in color with a dark brown mark in the shape of the letter Y. This frog lives in evergreen forests on mountains. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
